@NODE Main "LZX Repacker"

@{u}@{b}LZX Repacker  By @{"Christer Bjarnemo" link Author}@{ub} (v2.04b)@{uu}

Based on REPACK by Mat Bettinson of the Plot Hatching Factory.

  @{"  " link Disclaimer} Read this first!
   @{"  " link Introduction} Introduction
    @{"  " link Requirements} Requirements
     @{"  " link Usage} Usage
      @{"  " link History} History

Please note that this guide WORDWRAPS all texts... (Try to resize the window and see) You other guys who are writing guides, please do the same and use @{b}@wordwrap@{ub} in the header..

@endnode

;##########################################################################

@node Introduction

What will these scripts do? They will simply repack all those old @{b}LZH/LHA/ZIP/ARC/ARJ/ZOO/GZ/Z@{ub} archives into the superior @{b}LZX@{ub}.

And yes, @{b}LHA2LZX@{ub} can also repack those useless @{b}DMS@{ub} files...

@endnode

;##########################################################################

@node USAGE

 1> @{b}LHA2LZX@{ub} <directory> [options]

Where options could be the following:

@{u}@{b}FORCELZX@{uu}@{ub}
Allways keep the LZX file, even if it was bigger than the old archive.

@{u}@{b}KEEPOLD@{uu}@{ub}
Also keep both the old file and the new LZX file.

@{u}@{b}ONLYLHA@{uu}@{ub}
Only repack LhA files.

@{u}@{b}DMS@{uu}@{ub}
Also repack DMS archives. This should be used with caution, since some DMS files are Non-dos.

@endnode

;##########################################################################

@node Disclaimer

Use this program on your own risk. Im not responsible if it screws your, or your computers soft/hardware. :-)

@endnode

;##########################################################################

@node Requirements

To run @{b}LhA2LZX@{ub}, you must have the following:

* @{b}WB 2.04@{ub}

* @{b}AREXX@{ub}

* @{b}LZX, LHA, UNDMS, UNZIP, UNARJ, ARC, ZOO, GZIP@{ub} and @{b}UNCOMPRESS@{ub}... (most of them included here)

* @{b}FMS, RAD:@{ub} or a similar virtual disk unit if you are going to convert @{b}DMS@{ub} archives. You could ofcourse use @{b}DF0:@{ub} but it would be quite slow. To @{b}change DEVICE@{ub}, just load the main @{b}LHA2LZX@{ub} file into an editor..

@endnode

